From: gt8134b@prism.gatech.EDU (Robert Sanders)
Subject: Re: Linux IS well documented.
Date: 5 Dec 93 04:49:34 GMT

markline@henson.cc.wwu.edu (Mark Line) writes:

[perhaps misled, but not nearly offensive, thread deleted]

>NO, NO, NO!!! DON'T YOU UNDERSTAND? LINUX IS THE *PRIVATE* TERRITORY
>OF HACKERS!!! ONLY HACKERS!!! ONLY HACKERS!!! Hackers *always* just
>read the source code. GUIs are for sissies. Anybody who does not just
>type shell commands from within vi is a SISSY!!!! SISSIERS DON'T
>DESERVE TO BE USERS OF LINUX!!!!! ONLY HACKERS!!! ONLY HACKERS!!!

>That's easy! Read the source code until you find out. And besides,
>real hackers never have to delete lines in vi. They always write everything
>*perfectly* the first time. Don't you? HACKERS RULE!!!!!!

Dear me, someone's a bit trigger happy.  I guess you had a pocketful
of sarcasm and just *had* to use it up.

The contention that Linux is well documented because source is available
obviously doesn't work very well for non-programmers, but there is
still a valid point in there: if the documentation for HP-UX isn't
good enough, you're out of luck.  If the docs for Linux aren't up to
snuff, you can always get the information you need from reading the
source.

There are enough flamewars over real issues; please don't lower the
already abysmal signal:noise ratio on this hierarchy.

